The idea of Moloch, as presented by Scott Alexander in his 2014 essay is becoming increasingly relevant today, where polarization and mistrust, tribalism, climate change, and issues of personal safety are at the forefront of societal concerns. Moloch represents a dynamic where people, acting rationally in their individual interests, inadvertently cause collectively negative outcomes. This concept can be applied to a wide range of areas, such as environmental policies, economic systems, foreign relations, and more.
